sub_title: MA Social Sciences & Business SBS / L.L. B.
summary:
Interdisciplinary Master student in Social Sciences & Business with a focus on development studies, law, psychology & politics. Currently, I am based in Kigali working on my master’s thesis. It focuses on the differences in education systems of several elementary schools in Tanzania, Uganda and Rwanda. After that I will start a Master’s in Human Rights. 

Additionally, I have finished my Bachelor’s Degree in Law at in Rwanda (with a focus on Rwandan Labor Law, as well as International and Dutch Law). 

I have completed several volunteering and fundraising projects in East-Africa in the past two years. Due to the nature of this work and my studies, I have become passionate about social development projects as well as advocating for human rights.
